Eivind Holt Solberg (22 May 1933 – 19 March 2008) was a Norwegian jazz trumpeter, known as the founder of Big Chief Jazz Band (1952 -), which is one of the oldest of its kind.
He initially played in New Orleans Hot Dogs (1950–1951) with friends from Berg Upper Secondary School.
